We recommended to the Local Chief Executive to:
Require the Acting Municipal Treasurer to generate and maintain a summary of the Report of Collections and Deposits (RCDs) daily from the ETRACS and to ensure timely and accurate reporting and depositing of collections to the bank;
Direct all Collecting Officers including the Municipal Treasurer to prepare RCD on a daily basis, reflecting the actual date of collection;
Direct the Municipal Treasurer to verify the Report of Collections and Deposits remitted by collectors and monitor the issuances of accountable forms; and
Install and strictly observe internal control over cash collections to adequately safeguard government funds and records from possible misuse and losses.

